<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="lend-vt">lend <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /lend/    美 /lend/  </p>
<p>(lent, lent)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>借出；把...借给</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>lend sb sth / lend sth to sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you lend me some money? / Could you lend some money to me?
你能借给我些钱吗？</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="give-lend-sb-a-hand">give / lend (sb) a hand</h3>
<p>1.<strong>帮助 (某人)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I saw two men pushing a broken-down car so I stopped to lend (them) a hand.
我看到两个人正在推一辆抛锚的车，于是停下来帮他们。</p></div>

<h3 id="lend-borrow">辨析 lend, borrow</h3>
<p><strong>二者都译为“借”，但意义不同。</strong> </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You mustn't <strong>lend</strong> the book <strong>to</strong> others.
不许你把这本书借给别人。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He decided to <strong>borrow</strong> some money <strong>from</strong> the bank.
他决定到银行贷点款。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>If you are in trouble, Mike is always willing to <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (帮忙). (lend)  （2013 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. lend a hand  </p></div>